didn't know he was expecting you.

95
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:27,945
Well he isn't.

96
00:13:29,392 --> 00:13:32,264
- Could we sit?
- Sure.

97
00:13:32,343 --> 00:13:34,642
Would you like some tea?

98
00:13:34,891 --> 00:13:36,839
No thank you.

99
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:41,821
I know this sounds impossibly British, but
I can't bring myself to drink tea from a mug.

100
00:13:41,836 --> 00:13:45,106
- Is that terrible?
- No, of course not.

101
00:13:46,794 --> 00:13:52,022
How's Jason? I haven't spoken to him since
he left Paris...

102
00:13:52,031 --> 00:13:56,353
And he won't answer any of my calls.
I'm afraid that...

103
00:13:56,412 --> 00:14:01,094
- I am afraid he thinks that I'm angry with him.
- You're not?

104
00:14:01,417 --> 00:14:04,374
I simply want to see him again.

105
00:14:04,569 --> 00:14:09,351
Mrs. Teague, I...
I've wanted to meet you.

106
00:14:09,453 --> 00:14:14,787
But if Jason isn't ready to be a part of
your life, I don't think I can either.

107
00:14:15,576 --> 00:14:18,565
Not behind his back.

108
00:14:19,245 --> 00:14:24,202
The last thing I want to do is put you in
the middle of this, but...

109
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:30,382
If you could just tell him that I'm here,
and that I'm staying at the Smallville Inn.

110
00:14:30,454 --> 00:14:33,716
Tell him I want to see him.

111
00:14:33,887 --> 00:14:35,863
Sure.

112
00:14:35,938 --> 00:14:37,477
Thanks.

113
